booting process of rhel 8

post =====power on self test, each hardware componets test there own to power on  if it is ok then to bios

bios====basic i/o of the system, loads all the info of the hardware

mbr-=== master boot recorder is the first sector of the  hard disk holds  512 bytes it checks.where boot files are located 
        Primary boot loader info in 1st 446 bytes
         Partition table info in next 64 bytes
        MBR validation check in last 2 bytes.
        It contains information about GRUB2 (GRUB or LILO in old systems).
         So, in simple terms MBR loads and executes the GRUB2 boot loader.

grub2(version 2)== loads configuration from /boot/grub2/grub.conf  it provides option to selet kernel to boot  loads kernel and initramfs 

kernel===kernel execute /sbin/init from intramfs as the first process and pid is 1 
          While system starting kernel loads all the necessary Kernel Modules and Drives from initrd.img to load system first process systemd pid is 1
         on rhel init is replaced with systemd so /sbin/init is a soft link to systemd
